  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b85\u0bb3\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc7 \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Limited number of buses are in service",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The All Sri Lankan Private Bus Owners Association has stated that from today only buses of less than 50% capacity can be put into service nationwide.",
        "Kemunu Wijeratne, President of the All Sri Lanka Private Bus Owners Association said that this situation has occurred due to the fuel crisis in the country.",
        "He said that for the last three days diesel supply was not carried out in a proper manner and due to this the bus was not put into full service yesterday. (a)"
      ],
